    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/morrison-cou1-decision-2026",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/morrison-credibility-assessment-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The credibility body of evidence for the Morrison CFD hemolysis model is judged to support a Medium assurance level. Seven of thirteen credibility factors were formally assessed; all assessed factors meet or exceed required levels for MRL 2. Validation activities directly address the COU QoI using the same geometry and overlapping operating conditions. Grid convergence is well-characterized with GCI below 10%. Output comparison metrics (MAPE 8.3%, NIA 0.91) demonstrate adequate predictive accuracy for the regulatory decision. The six non-assessed factors are appropriately scoped out at MRL 2. The credibility assessment team concludes that the evidence is sufficient to accept the model for use in identifying worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for the Class II CPB device.",
